The article discusses an Executive Order signed by President Obama to strengthen protections against human trafficking in federal contracts. It emphasizes the importance of combating human trafficking and ensuring that American tax dollars do not contribute to this issue. The Executive Order prohibits contractors and subcontractors from engaging in specific trafficking-related activities, such as fraudulent recruitment practices and charging employees recruitment fees. It also introduces tailored compliance measures for larger contracts performed abroad, requiring contractors to maintain compliance plans and certify that they have not engaged in trafficking-related activities. Additionally, the Executive Order establishes a process to identify industries and sectors with a history of human trafficking and enhances training and monitoring to address trafficking violations.